A variety of musics by the Mang'anja, Yao and Cewa peoples, found in the 1950's in the southern half of Malawi - the beautiful bangwe zither, the magnificent tuned drum likhuba ensembles, brilliant xylophone playing, a small big band of kazoos. 

Historical recordings by Hugh Tracey.
